    <summary>Defines the polling modes for the <see cref="M:System.Net.Sockets.Socket.Poll(System.Int32,System.Net.Sockets.SelectMode)" /> method.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 The <xref:System.Net.Sockets.SelectMode> enumeration defines the polling modes that can be passed to the <xref:System.Net.Sockets.Socket.Poll%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method. Use the SelectRead value to determine if a listening <xref:System.Net.Sockets.Socket> has incoming connection requests. Use the SelectWrite value to determine if a <xref:System.Net.Sockets.Socket> is writeable. Use the SelectError value to determine if there is an error condition present on the <xref:System.Net.Sockets.Socket>. For explanations of writeability, readability, and the presence of error conditions, see the <xref:System.Net.Sockets.Socket.Poll%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method.  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 The following example checks the status of a <xref:System.Net.Sockets.Socket> using all three <xref:System.Net.Sockets.SelectMode> enumeration values. A call to <xref:System.Net.Sockets.Socket.Poll%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> using the SelectWrite enumerated value should return `true`.  
  
